---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const snapshot = [
  { label: "Industry", value: "Life Sciences / Enterprise SaaS" },
  { label: "Role", value: "Director of Product Design" },
  { label: "Scope", value: "8 designers, 3 researchers, cross-functional leadership" },
  { label: "Key Outcomes", value: "50% faster design-to-development, 65% faster task completion" },
];

const decisions = [
  {
    title: "Explainability-first AI interactions",
    text: "We treated AI support as a decision aid, not a black box—designing for clarity, trust, and human oversight in high-stakes workflows.",
  },
  {
    title: "Task-centric workflow structure",
    text: "We shifted the experience away from data-heavy screens toward workflow-oriented paths that matched how clinical teams actually work.",
  },
  {
    title: "Component-first platform design",
    text: "We established reusable interaction and UI patterns that reduced fragmentation and improved scalability across product lines.",
  },
];

const outcomes = [
  "Reduced design-to-development cycle time by 50% through clearer systems, governance, and execution workflows.",
  "Improved user task completion time by 65% through simplified workflows and better information hierarchy.",
  "Supported enterprise-scale platform consistency with a design system adopted across product lines.",
  "Enabled AI-informed decision-making while maintaining transparency, usability, and regulatory confidence.",
];
---

<MainLayout title="AI-Powered Life Sciences Platform | Jorge Obando">
  <section class="case-study-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">SAAMA</p>
      <h1>AI-Powered Life Sciences Platform</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Reframing fragmented clinical research workflows into a scalable enterprise platform
        that improved efficiency, reduced complexity, and enabled more confident,
        AI-informed decision-making.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="snapshot-grid" aria-label="Case study snapshot">
      {snapshot.map((item) => (
        <article class="snapshot-card">
          <p class="snapshot-label">{item.label}</p>
          <p class="snapshot-value">{item.value}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The situation</h2>
      <p>
        Clinical trial professionals were operating across fragmented legacy systems,
        overloaded interfaces, and disconnected workflows. Critical information was spread
        across multiple tools, making routine work slower, more error-prone, and harder to
        manage at scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        As organizations pushed for faster, more intelligent clinical operations, the need
        was not simply for a better interface. The need was for a unified platform that
        could reduce cognitive load, support regulatory rigor, and make AI useful in
        everyday decision-making.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The core challenge was to simplify highly complex, data-dense workflows without
        oversimplifying the reality of clinical research operations. Teams needed faster
        access to information, clearer prioritization, and confidence in the system’s
        recommendations—especially where compliance and auditability mattered.
      </p>
      <p>
        This meant solving for more than usability. It required aligning workflow design,
        information architecture, governance, and platform consistency across an enterprise
        environment with multiple user roles, evolving requirements, and AI-enabled
        capabilities.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        As Director of Product Design, I operated across product strategy, design
        leadership, and systems governance. I guided designers and researchers, aligned
        cross-functional stakeholders, and helped shape a platform direction that could
        scale across modules, teams, and operational contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        My role was not limited to interface decisions. It included creating the structure,
        standards, and decision frameworks needed to reduce fragmentation and improve how
        product, design, and engineering worked together.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How I operated</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid two-up">
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Clarified the real problem</h3>
          <p>
            We reframed the work from “modernizing screens” to improving end-to-end
            clinical workflows, reducing cognitive load, and making decision support more usable.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Structured the system</h3>
          <p>
            We used information hierarchy, modular patterns, and design system thinking to
            create a more coherent platform foundation across products and roles.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Aligned stakeholders</h3>
          <p>
            I worked across product, engineering, and design to build shared understanding
            around priorities, constraints, and platform direction.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Drove execution</h3>
          <p>
            We translated strategy into production-ready systems, reducing rework and
            increasing consistency from design through implementation.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Key decisions</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid one-up">
        {decisions.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.text}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-card">
        <ul>
          {outcomes.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Reflection</h2>
      <p>
        This work demonstrates the kind of design leadership I bring to complex
        environments: not just improving interfaces, but building the systems,
        governance, and cross-functional clarity needed to make platforms more usable,
        scalable, and strategically valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section next-step">
      <h2>Next case study</h2>
      <p>
        Continue to <a href="/case-studies/smb-marketplace-fintech">SMB Marketplace & Fintech Ecosystem</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a33a3a;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4.15rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .snapshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .snapshot-card,
  .info-card,
  .outcomes-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .snapshot-card {
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .snapshot-label {
    margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #777;
  }

  .snapshot-value {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #222;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 2.2vw, 2.4rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  }

  .content-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: 840px;
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cards-grid.two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .cards-grid.one-up {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .info-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .info-card p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .outcomes-card {
    padding: 1.35rem 1.4rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  .outcomes-card li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .next-step a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.15em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .snapshot-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-page {
      padding: 1.5rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .snapshot-grid,
    .cards-grid.two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }
  }
</style>